  "debug_data_path": "debug_data/2020_719",
  "eprint": {
    "title": "Hypercube and Cascading-based Algorithms for Secret Sharing Schemes",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Shion Samadder Chaudhury",
        "email": "shion@gmail",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Sabyasachi Dutta",
        "email": "math@gmail",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Kouichi Sakurai",
        "email": "comsakurai@inf",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "Secret sharing is a very useful way to maintain secrecy of private data when\nstored in a distributed way among several nodes. Two significant questions\nin this area are 1. how to accommodate new nodes and assign shares to the\nnew nodes, the problem becomes harder if the number of joining nodes or the\naccess structure is not known in advance and can be (potentially) unbounded\nand 2. to reduce the computational complexity of secret sharing schemes. In\nthis paper we propose two new constructions of such secret sharing schemes\nbased on different combinatorial structures. The first construction is based\non generalized paths joining the opposite vertices of a hypercube which has\nbeen divided into smaller hypercubes. The second construction is a forest-\nbased construction utilizing a dynamic data structure technique known as\nfractional cascading. The generalized path we call a pavement is new to this\npaper. Both our constructions use a new secret redistribution scheme to\nassign and re-assign shares to nodes. Towards the second question we show\nthat allowing certain trade-offs, the constructions are implementable by $AC^0$\ncircuits which is the lowest complexity class in which secret sharing and\nreconstruction is possible. To the best of the knowledge of the authors, none\nof the similar existing schemes (evolving or dynamic) are $AC^0$ computable\nand this paper for the first time combines the idea of hypercubes and dynamic\ndata structures with secret sharing for preserving long-term confidentiality of secret data.",
    "keywords": [
      "Hypercube",
      "Forest",
      "Secret Sharing",
      "Error-Correcting Codes",
      "AC0 Circuits"
    ],
    "category": "Cryptographic protocols",
    "publication_info": "Preprint. MINOR revision.",
